to the editor re away from haiti discovering the politics of the possible public lives column may 19 the election of josaphat celestin as mayor of north miami has great symbolic and political value for all haitians in the united states and it attests to the resiliency of the american political system in its ability to turn any immigrant into a full fledged american but i believe that its most important effect will be felt in haiti as more haitians travel between the two countries and begin to bring back to the island the democratic ideals of tolerance compromise and justice francois pierre louis jamaica queens may 20 2001 the writer is an assistant professor of political science at queens college cuny

